24T19:24:33.519668Z","entity":"article","guid":"71518c6f-5861-40b8-8bda-3dd072d0c72f","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20161024-your-facebook-sharing-can-reveal-hidden-signals-about-you","modifiedDateTime":"2019-10-04T14:32:01.111235Z","project":"future","slug":"20161024-your-facebook-sharing-can-reveal-hidden-signals-about-you","cacheLastUpdated":1587442999743},"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet":{"urn":"urn:pubstack:jative:article:future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet","_id":"5e982097272a584021aaf639","ambientVideo":"","articleType":"story","assetVideo":null,"author":[],"bodyIntro":"Hundreds of millions of personal photos are uploaded to the web every day, but which one was the first? Rose Eveleth investigates.","businessUnit":"worldwide","cards":[{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIn 1989, Silvano de Gennaro, a computer scientist at the Cern laboratory in Switzerland, decided to start a music festival that still runs to this day. He called it the \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fhardronic.web.cern.ch\u002FHardronic\u002F2015\u002F\"\u003ECern Hardronic Festival\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and invited the Cern community to get up on stage and showcase their talents. Little did he know that his festival would lead to the creation of a girl group whose picture would be the \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fmusiclub.web.cern.ch\u002FMusiClub\u002Fbands\u002Fcernettes\u002Fpictures\u002FLHC5.jpg\"\u003Efirst personal photograph to be uploaded to the web\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMichele de Gennaro, who is now married to Silvano, remembers the first festival clearly. She was working as a bilingual secretary when a friend approached her about the show. Her friend planned to get Silvano to write a song to a particular physicist who she had her eye on, and wanted Michele to join her on stage.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo Silvano wrote a song called Collider, about a lonely woman whose partner works long shifts at &ndash; you guessed it &ndash; the collider. Watch it \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.youtube.com\u002Fwatch?v=1e1eLe1ihT0\"\u003Ehere.\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnfortunately, the desired physicist never actually saw the performance, Michele says, since he was on shift. &ldquo;It was a shame but we had a great time and we got a lot of attention from elsewhere,&rdquo; she says. Thus was born Les Horribles Cernettes (a play on Cern&rsquo;s Large Hadron Collider), a revolving group of female singers who donned big hair, vintage dresses, and sang songs about physics.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-0"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-1"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"This parody group with big hairdos and dresses reminiscent of the 50s, doing song of physics. I thought &lsquo;that&rsquo;s fantastic&rsquo; -&nbsp;Lynn Veronneau","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-2"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003ELynn Veronneau, then a research administrator at Cern, remembers seeing the Cernettes for the first time at a festival on the campus. &ldquo;I was there when these girls came on and I loved them!&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;This parody group with big hairdos and dresses reminiscent of the 50s, doing songs of physics. I thought &lsquo;that&rsquo;s fantastic&rsquo;. I was studying opera at the time and I thought &lsquo;I want to be in that band!&rsquo;&rdquo; A year later, she was one of the Cernettes.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOne day, Michele, Lynn, and the other Cernettes members at the time, were backstage at a gig, make-up done, ready to go on, when Silvano appeared with a camera. &ldquo;Okay girls, give me a shot for the album cover,&rsquo; he said. They posed, squatting together, with big smiles.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-3"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-4"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003ELater, Silvano was working on the photo on his computer &ndash; editing out the messy background so it could be used for the album cover &ndash; when \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20120703-how-i-turned-down-tim-berners-lee\"\u003ETim Berners-Lee\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, the inventor of the World Wide Web, walked into his office. When he saw the image, he told Silvano that he should make the Cernettes a website. &ldquo;I hardly knew what the web was,&rdquo; Silvano says. At the time his work involved running software on servers at Cern. &ldquo;I wasn&rsquo;t really working on it.&rdquo;&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-5"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"It was the photo that opened the web to life","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-6"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EBerners-Lee decided to create a webpage for all the social activities at Cern and he included the picture of the Cernettes on the page for the music club.&nbsp;This first version of the image was tiny by today&rsquo;s standards; in those days, the web couldn&rsquo;t handle large pictures. Silvano says that the image was probably 120 pixels by 50 pixels. &ldquo;It was the size of a stamp and took about one minute to load on your screen.&rdquo; Because they took so long to materialise, pictures didn&rsquo;t load on the website automatically, you had to click on them to get the image to appear.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-7"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-8"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EAlthough this photo of the Cernettes is commonly called &ldquo;the first photograph uploaded to the internet&rdquo; that&rsquo;s not completely accurate. For starters, the internet existed before the web. And as the web was built for physicists to share data, that data often included scientific images. There were loads of images already on the web long before the Cernettes&rsquo; photograph made its way there. But the photo of the four women is the first non-technical picture uploaded to the web. The first picture that was simply a photo for fun, not work. &ldquo;It was the photo that opened the web to life,&rdquo; says Silvano.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-9"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"It was the size of a stamp and took about one minute to load on your screen","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-10"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003ELynn didn&rsquo;t realise until about five years ago that the photo had a special place in history. Even then she says she didn&rsquo;t really understand what the big deal was. &ldquo;I was starting a big musical project and I remember having this conversation with our publicist at the time, who said, &lsquo;oh my god that&rsquo;s a piece of history, we&rsquo;ve got to put that in your bio.&rsquo;&rdquo; Now, Lynn embraces her part of history. &ldquo;I can tell my friends and family I was incredibly privileged to accidentally be in the first picture uploaded,&rdquo; she says.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen I asked Michele if she had any sense that the photo they were taking would become iconic she laughed. &ldquo;No of course not, no my goodness.&rdquo; But she says that, like Lynn, she now appreciates being a part of history.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-11"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-12"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"We look so beautiful and wonderful in that picture. I love it","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20160224-the-unlikely-photo-that-kickstarted-the-social-internet-13"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EToday, the Cernettes are scattered across the globe. Michele and Silvano live in Mauritius, where Michele is a pilates instructor. Lynn is a professional musician, who tours the world with her jazz band. Angela Higney, the Cernette on the left in the photo now lives in Glasgow and works as a vocal coach. Collete Marx-Nielsen, the woman in the silvery sequin dress, lives in France. In 2012, the original four Cernettes reunited at Cern, and were joined by a whole group of later Cernettes for a concert; Lynn says she was blown away by how excited people were. &ldquo;The response at the reunion concert was overwhelming. It was huge, there were so many people who came and there were a lot of people online &ndash; we webcast it and over 2000 people logged in.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is something very special about that first photo of the Cernettes, says Michele. &ldquo;It was maybe one of the first bands on the internet. We look so beautiful and wonderful in that picture. I love it.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003ECorrection: This article has been edited to reflect the difference between the web and the internet.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EJoin 500,000+ Future fans by liking us on\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002FBBCFuture\"\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFacebook\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cem\u003E, or follow us on\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Ftwitter.com\u002Fbbc_future\"\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETwitter\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cem\u003E,\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fplus.google.com\u002F107828172298602173375\u002Fposts\"\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGoogle+\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cem\u003E,\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.linkedin.com\u002Fcompany\u002Fbbc-com\"\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELinkedIn\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E&nbsp;\u003Cem\u003Eand\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Finstagram.com\u002Fbbcfuture_official\u002F\"\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInstagram\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EIf you liked this story, \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fpages.emails.bbc.com\u002Fsubscribe\u002F\"\u003Esign up for the weekly bbc.com features newsletter\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, called &ldquo;If You Only Read 6 Things This Week&rdquo;. A handpicked s